.SH "NAME"
colon \- Prepend (beginning, the default), append (end) or remove to colon variables (PATH, INFOPATH, MANPATH etc.)
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
\fBcolon\fP [\fIOPTION\fP]... [\fIFILE|DIR\fP] [\fIVALUE\fP]
\fBcolon\fP \-\-base
\fBcolon\fP \-\-bins [\fIFILE|DIR\fP]
\fBcolon\fP \-\-init
.fi
.br
.sp
\fBcolon\fP \-\-description|\-\-name|\-\-subsections|\-\-synopsis|\-\-desc|\-\-help|\-\-manrepo|\-\-version|...
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBcolon\fP command
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-\-append\fP
.RS 4
Append \fIFILE|DIR\fP argument (dirname if \fIFILE\fP)
to \fIVALUE\fP argument (if provided, otherwise returns the \fIFILE|DIR\fP argument).
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-base\fP
.RS 4
Shows the base \fI$PATH\fP, \fI$MANPATH\fP and \fI$INFOPATH\fP with \fI/\fP and \fI/usr\fP
as top directories to add:
\fI/bin\fP, \fI/sbin\fP, \fI/share/man\fP and \fI/share/info\fP.
.br
It implies the \fI\-\-export\fP option to be used with \f(CReval\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-bins\fP
.RS 4
The output (\fI\-\-export\fP option implied) will have \fI$PATH\fP, \fI$MANPATH\fP and \fI$INFOPATH\fP updated to be used with \fIeval\fP.
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
If \fBFILE|DIR\fP argument is a \fBDIR\fP, then \fBDIR\fP is prepended  to \fI$PATH\fP (unless \fBDIR\fP is the top of a git repository).
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
If \fBFILE|DIR\fP argument is a \fBFILE\fP, then \fBparent of FILE\fP is prepended to \fI$PATH\fP
(unless \fBparent of FILE\fP is the top of a git repository).
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fIgit top\fP if no \fBFILE|DIR\fP argument is provided
or parent directory of one of the two previous bullet items is used
to add: \fI/bin\fP, \fI/sbin\fP, \fI/share/man\fP and \fI/share/info\fP to \fI$PATH\fP,
\fI$MANPATH\fP (even if directory does not exist, since contents are generated)
and \fI$INFOPATH\fP.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
If a \fI./tests\fP directory exists, then previous bullet items subdirectories will be added with \fI./tests/\fP.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-export\fP, *\-\-export=*\fI[VARIABLE NAME]\fP
.RS 4
Show the output with \fIexport command\fP to be used with \fIeval\fP with \fIVARIABLE NAME\fP if provided (default: \fI$PATH\fP).
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-init\fP
.RS 4
Shows initial \fI$PATH\fP, \fI$MANPATH\fP, and \fI$INFOPATH\fP.
.br
It also shows:  \fI$TOP\fP and \fI$<REPO_BASENAME>_TOP\fP which contain the \fIgit top\fP for \fBcolon\fP command.
.br
It implies the \fI\-\-export\fP option to be used with \f(CReval\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-P\fP, \fB\-\-physical\fP
.RS 4
Use physical absolute directories instead of symlink \fIpwd \-P\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-remove\fP
.RS 4
Remove \fIFILE|DIR\fP argument (dirname if \fIFILE\fP)
from \fIVALUE\fP argument (if provided, otherwise returns empty).
.RE
